Wolfblade::

She squeezed Malice's hand back. She nodded her approval to return to
base.


--- In nbwrpg@yahoogroups.com, robert riley <bustercross365@y...> wrote:
> Malice/ Hellplague:
>  
> Seeing Wolfblade's look, he smiled a bit and gave her hand a small
squeeze.
>  
> "If there is nothing else, let's get going, I don't like being out
here."
>  
>  
> Hellplague waited while Celeron complied with Malice's request. 
Once he was ready, she looked to Malice.
>  
> "Alright, let's go, I have a feeling your commander will be wanting
to talk to me."
> 
> Dark Mouse <raccoon7679@y...> wrote:
> Wolfblade::
> 
> She smiled a bit, and relaxed, just a bit. "Look, we're all on the
> same side. A Warrior's code is his bond and his word. By the Old
> Warrior's Code of Cybertron, I will not shoot unless shot at first.
> There, happy now?" She let a slightly playful smirk cross her face
> plates.  She wanted to know that she would give a sign of trust.
> She looked over and smiled at Malice. Her optics gave him a loving
> flash, then she looked at her two new comrads in arms. 
> 
> 
> "HA!  Is that all you got?  You boasted such power, such skill! 
Where is your power and skill now?  You disappoint me, ha ha ha haa!"
